the cast order of the cast
value_description:
commonsense evidence:
The cast order of a movie or television show refers to the sequence in which the actors and actresses are listed in the credits. This order is typically determined by the relative importance of each actor's role in the production, with the main actors and actresses appearing first, followed by the supporting cast and extras.
